==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adessenarian
<hw>Ad*es`se*na"ri*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formed
fr. L. <ets>adesse</ets> to be present; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>esse</ets>
to be.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One who held the real
presence of Christ's body in the eucharist, but not by
transubstantiation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adfected</ent>⟦br⟧
